	   <a name=104125310332936></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104125310332936><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104125310332936>RE: need advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104125310332936#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=152893><span id=Scholar>Tibayn</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>37 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 30th 8:24 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.13]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To be honest, I have never been rich and never twinked a character, so I might not be the best person to talk to but I find that leveling is the best way to make money.<br><br>At your level, I would head to Paludal Caverns on the moon.&nbsp;&nbsp;Camp the first tunnel by the Hollowshade Moors exit.  There are a bunch of bugs (delvers) and a mushroom (reishi).  The Shrooms are the main target.  They are not social.  Be very careful of the bugs.  They are social and tend to flee and grab more.  You have to keep them rooted and figure out which are in each others aggro range.<br><br>You will learn a pattern of splitting the ones you can and killing the shroom.  Once they get light blue use inviso to to sneak past the lake full of phlergs (very dangerous, very social and a spread a long lasting disease).  Take the south tunnel (directly opposite the first tunnel) and you will find a tunnel that leads to a cavern with a shroom at each end.  Keep going down that tunnel and you will find a tunnel with 2 shrooms next to each other (again, not social).  This is the bananza, keep going back and forth, killing all 4 shrooms.  If you follow the tunnel further it has a branch full of phlergs (nastier bigger brother of phlargs, or is it vice versa, I forget).  The main tunnel ends with a group of Dwarven miners.<br><br>Starting with the Moors exit and ending with the miners is the best place for you.  It can take you to your early 20's in short time.  Loot is not good, but can be sold in the outpost in Moors.  I would stay away from phlargs and phlergs, but you can single pull a few when you are waiting for shrooms.  Try and get a resist before hand.<br><br>Once in your 20's, you can hit the bandit camps in PC, near SH.  You can make over 150pp an hour and level into your mid 20's.<br><br>Good luck.  Go forth and nuke.<br>&nbsp;<br>Larrymichaelson = 50th Human Wizard<br>Tibayn = 30th Vah Sir Beastlord<br>Oberlin = 8th Dwarf Cleric<br>Haarbinjer = 8th Erud Necro</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
