	   <tr><td colspan=2>1) Dont get fooled by the immediate rush for base int when starting - You will be greatful when you hit lvl 60 in a decent guild :)<br><br>2) Get your transmute staff - questable - it is the single most important item for a wizard.<br><br>3) learn how to play in conjunction with cleric heals on the MT (main tank)- there are many untold secrets about how to make mobs give up and run (hopefully snared) even at two bubs of hp! This skill will be invaluable in the planes where most mobs will enrage if things are not timed properly. A good wizard cleric combo will prevent nine in ten mobs enraging :)<br><br>4) Appreciate that patience and timing for a wizard is the hardest skill to learn but is the most valuable - timing of nukes is everything and the game rewards properly timed nukes too!<br><br>5) Post 50 exp - start in the hole on elementals. Zonein is always busy and there is a reason why :)<br>This dungeon is perfectly tailored to take a 50 up to 58 and you may even be lucky to purchase a manastone- which still works in this zone :) Combine its use with your epic rune and you will not be oom for long.<br><br>Fortunbas Soulsender<br>62 Pitted Iron Ring Sorceror<br>Officer- Shadows of Doom<br>Antonius Bayle<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
