	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've just created my first caster for something different to play to my other 2 char's.&nbsp;&nbsp;I selected a wiz mostly because I haven't run accross too many of them in the game and thought it might be good to play something different.  The thing I want to ask though is am I using the right tactic for a low level wiz?  At level 1 I got a staff off a skellie that I killed.  Since getting it, I've found that using spells to pull with and tanking mobs after I get their attention is by far the fastest method to level.  Less down time as I don't seem to get hit all that much and save on having to med.  Sped things up amazingly prior to level 4, but still seems quite a bit quicker than medding afterwards.  It took me about 6 hours of game time to go from level 2 to 6.<br><br>If this is the right tactic for now, at what level should I start moving to the root and nuke style of playing a wiz?  The main reason I haven't done this yet is that root still seems to take quite alot of mana for my char to cast.  Is root and nuke a good method to play a wiz or is there another that I haven't noticed yet?<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>40 season Half Elf Ranger <br>8 song Var Shir Bard <br>level 6 gnome wizard<br>Kayne Bayle Server</td></tr>
