	   <tr><td colspan=2>well at lvl 52 to 55 and 55 to say 59 were a lil harder then the rest of the lvls.. not because they take alot of time.. but fighting for the solo camps can be a real pain.. adventuring around killing npcs is actually a good idea.. but be careful.. as you will find some mobs begin to summon around that lvl lol.. summon = bad news for wiz.. i personally did the nobles .. in hhk to 54.. only took a few days of xping .. the hard part was gettin the camp.. go upstairs in high hold keep.. and walk around a bit on the 2nd floor u will find two nobles in one room.. issabella and two bards.. the nobles are on a 5 min repop.. and bards 18min i believe.. veryyy good xp here.. <br>now listen up since pop.. theres been imo a few things changing.. once you get to lvl 60.. your gonna wanna work on both lvl 61 and the poj trials.. if you dont know what that is.. dont worry you will find out.. get 61 before you try them.. helps ubber with resists.. but imo you should be a master wiz before attempting.. the reason i point this out.. <br>the nobles in hhk are some of the fastest lvl 51 AA fighting in the game.. i have friends that have racked up 50aa there at lvl 51.. imo for a wiz.. who wants to eventually be able to not only find a group in second tiers and on in POP you should start thinking about making yourself a DPS player.. yes lvls are still more important.. but by lvl 60 you need to make sure your DPS *damage per second* is higher then the average wiz.. do this by gaining advancements in AA and lvl 51 is the best time to start cause u still have DB nobles with great aa xp on them.. <br>gl to you awesome=) may lvl 65 be swift n painless! but full of adventure! =D<br>taygarr<br>wiz of the 61st season<br>the seventh hammer<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
