	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104022296066325><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104022296066325>RE: quad kiting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=104022296066325#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=162281><span id= >awesome</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>71 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 18th 10:14 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK first thing to do is not use rain spells while kiting. Circle of Force(lvl 34 spell) has a good dmg to mana ratio and i like to use it. Any pillar spells or column spells IMHO are good also for kiting. <br>OK a Point Blank AOE(PBAOE) is a spell that you must be close enough to be able to smell the bad breath the mobs have. These spells do not harm you in any way other than getting hit by the mob. The great thing about these spells is the only limitation to the number of mobs you can hit is the range of the spell. <br>A normal AOE--if the mobs are pounding on you and you cast it, you will take dmg from your spell. You DO NOT have to be close to the mob to cast this spell. <br>I think all the &quot;________ Spiral of Al'Kabor&quot; spells are a waste. You spend more mana than you do dmg to the mob. The only reason i have any of these is to practice my research.<br><br>Smackin Mobsaround &lt;Merciless Elites&gt;<br>52 season of being a wizzy<br>Terris Thule<br><br>Kill all the opposes our cause...ah f_@k that kill everything!!!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
