	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 30th 9:28 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>How much you can nuke without pulling aggro, depends on your level in the group and how much damage the tanks are doing.&nbsp;&nbsp;I never pull, that builds a big pile of aggro to overcome. My first spell almost always a stun, it parks the mob, while the tank deals out some damage without getting hurt.  This saves healer manna and builds aggro on to the main tank, then use a few small nukes, if you have manna or sit, until stun becomes available again if you don't, then stand and stun again.  Then towards the end, take out the mob with a big nuke.  You need to learn to estimate mob HPs and the tank damaging rate to time this correctly. Ideally it should use up virtually your whole nuke to kill it dead. You can still pull a mob even at this stage if you get it wrong.<br><br>I also try to keep some manna spare for overpulls, thats when your big nukes really pay for themselves. I always announce stuns and my biggest nukes, hoping someone will root as my biggest nukes fall, but havnt got it just right yet. People so far; forget in the heat of battle.<br><br>And for those times when you do get it wrong, get the best buffs you can from fellow groupies especially SoW and AC buffs. Then root the mob straight away, dont rely on others to pull it off, root is far quicker and hard to interupt.<br><br>EthelDave<br>36 Wizard on Karana<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Dec 30 09:10:36 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
