	   <a name=103880834421988></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103880834421988><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=103880834421988>RE: Lookin to start a wizard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=103880834421988#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=175564><span id= >Malimo</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 2nd 12:52 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well good for you, you cant beat a wizard.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; Obviously the number 1 stat you will need for a wizard is INT.  Although int stuff is pretty easy to come by so it is not sooo important to pick a class with high int on it.  A lot of people like to play DE's for the Ultravision, but I don't think that ofsets the faction issues to deal with.  As for equipment, anything with int on it obviously.  A stein of Moggok is an easy way to get a good amount of INT.  One item that would be immensly helpful if you can find one is a Solist's Icy Wand.  They drop in kurns tower in the Field of Bone.  They are quite rare though but you should be able to buy one in the bazaar for about 4000pp or so.  I am not quite sure on all the stats, but it has an unlimited right click 4 second cast 34dd that can be used from level 12 on.  At level 12 being able to constantly nuke for 34dammage with no mana is invaluable.  You will want to get your staff of temperate flux as soon as possable as well.  This has an instant cast right click fire and cold debuff.  But its real use is for a mana free pulling tool that can be done on the run and it also serves as a range finder for kiting.  Most people try to quest it in their mid 20's  you need a heart of fire from goblin wizards in naggy's layer, and a heart of frost from goblin wizards in permafrost.  the last thing you need is a lambent stone.  the hearts are no drop, as is the staff.  For any more info in being a wizzard go to www.graffe.com.  One of the best places to solo at 25 is lake of ill omen.  Just get yourself SOW and quad kite anything you can find that is blue to even con.  Just try and get all the same thing in each quad and avoid sarnaks that are actualy inside the fort as there are casters in there.  those will take you to 29 in a big hurry.  from there do gnolls in south karana till about 34 or so.  or higer, but it gets slow.  From there if you can get KEI you can quad specters in oasis all the way up to about 48 with good speed.  Just do it at full speed and dont use bonds of force at least untilla bout 42 otherwise you will be getting a lot of resists on it and it will be a pain in the rear.  Once you get to 48 and specs get slow you can go to TD right from oasis and do spirocs.  They run fast so you will have to snare them, but they are not nearly as resistant as the specs and even on the provens you shouldnt have to wory abuot geting resisted.  They will take you all the way to 51 but start slowing down after that.  I have been grouping up in the new planes from there so I have not found a new place to solo yet.  Alot of people say raptors in TD or drakes in CS if you have descent COV faction.  I hope this helps.  Oh yea. . . Get J-Boots.<br>&nbsp;<br>&lt;html&gt;<br>&lt;embed src="<a href="http://archimagus.50megs.com/pictures/malsig1.swf"" target=_new>http://archimagus.50megs.com/pictures/malsig1.swf"</a> height="200" width="600"&gt;<br>&lt;/embed&gt;<br>&lt;/html&gt;</td></tr>
